<li id="cite_note-92"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-92">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFGerrish2004">Gerrish 2004</a>, pp.&#160;290–291, 302. According to Gerrish, Calvin put his defence against the charge of novelty in the preface of every edition of the <i>Institutes</i>. The original preface of the first edition was addressed to the King of France, Francis I. The defence expressed his opinion that patristic authority favoured the reformers and that allegation of the reformers deviating from the patristic consensus was a fiction. See also <a href="#CITEREFSteinmetz1995">Steinmetz 1995</a>, pp.&#160;122–137.</span>
